parameters.name: SC_X
parameters.description: Spacecraft X position in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of astronomical units.  The X axis points towards the the first point of Aries in the solar equatorial plane on the vernal equinox of the reference epoch 1950 (positive away from the Sun).

parameters.name: SC_Y
parameters.description: Spacecraft Y position in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of astronomical units.  The Y axis completes the right handed set.

parameters.name: SC_Z
parameters.description: Spacecraft Z position in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of astronomical units.  The Z axis points along the Sun's spin axis (positive above the equatorial plane).

parameters.name: VEL_X
parameters.description: Spacecraft velocity X component in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of kilometers/second.  The X axis points towards the the first point of Aries in the solar equatorial plane on the vernal equinox of the reference epoch 1950 (positive away from the Sun).

parameters.name: VEL_Y
parameters.description: Spacecraft velocity Y component in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of kilometers/second. The Y axis completes the right handed set.

parameters.name: VEL_Z
parameters.description: Spacecraft velocity Z component in Heliographic (RTN) coordinates in units of kilometers/second. The Z axis points along the Sun's spin axis (positive above the equatorial plane).

parameters.name: SC_R
parameters.description: Heliocentric range from Sun to spacecraft in units of astronomical units (1 AU = 149674000 km).

parameters.name: SC_LAT
parameters.description: Spacecraft heliocentric latitude, the angle between the plane containing the solar spin axis and the solar equatorial plane (positive above the equatorial plane), in degrees.

parameters.name: SC_LON
parameters.description: Spacecraft heliocentric longitude (increasing in the direction of planetary orbital motion) in degrees.

parameters.name: SOLEQUATORIAL_TO_HG
parameters.description: This column contains the 9 1pe15.8 rotation matrix elements for converting from Solar Equatorial to Heliographic coordinates.

parameters.name: HG_TO_EARTHORBTRUE
parameters.description: This column contains the 9 1pe15.8 rotation matrix elements for converting from Heliographic to Earth Orbit True coordinates.

parameters.name: SPACECRAFT_TO_HG
parameters.description: This column contains the 9 1pe15.8 rotation matrix elements for converting from Payload (Spacecraft) to Heliographic coordinates.
